                "href": "/profile/Shreya-Ghatuary"
            },
            "answer_text": "Lone pair is a pair of electrons in a molecule, that does not take part in a chemical bonding. Basically, pair of electrons which do not form any kind of bond in a molecule. For example, in H20, oxygen has 6 electrons in outermost shell and it uses 2 electrons to form a single bond with each hydrogen atom. 6 - 2 = 4, hence, 4 electrons are now left which do not form any bond. These electrons are represented in form of pairs. Hence in H20, oxygen has 4 non bonding electrons or 2 lone pairs. ",
